Taking values between 5 and 95 percentile¶

In [6]:
low = .05
high = 0.95
quant_df = data.quantile([low, high])
In [7]:
new_data = data.apply(lambda x: x[(x>quant_df.loc[low,x.name]) & (x < quant_df.loc[high,x.name])], axis=0)
In [8]:

plt.subplots(figsize = (40,40))
for i in range(16):
    plt.subplot(4,4,i+1)
    plt.plot(month_data[month_data.columns[i]])
    plt.title(month_data.columns[i])
    plt.xlabel("Months")
plt.show()

Make pie charts for different weather conditions in a month.¶

In [20]:
data = pd.read_csv("delhi-weather-data\\testset.csv", parse_dates=['datetime_utc'],index_col='datetime_utc')
data.columns = data.columns.str.replace(" _","")
data['month'] = data.index.month
In [21]:
data = data[['conds','month']]
In [22]:
group = data.groupby(['month'])
In [28]:
months = ['January','February','March','April','May','June','July','August','September','October','November','December']
In [39]:
plt.subplots(figsize = (40,40))
for mon,grp in group:
    plt.subplot(4,3,mon)
    grp['conds'].value_counts()[:7].plot(kind='pie', autopct="%1.1f%%" )
    plt.title(months[mon-1])
plt.show()
